    • numberButtons

      public static void numberButtons​(int i, java.lang.String textFieldGetter)
      numberButtons method writes numbers to the text field if the conditions are okay. If 0 is seen on the screen, number will not be added to the right, it will be replaced with 0. If there is an error on the text field, number will not be added to field. While adding numbers, thousand separators will be seen.
      Parameters:
      i - and textFieldGetter because i brings the number of the button, and text field reaches here from GUI via getter.

    • decimalButton

    • deleteButton

      public static void deleteButton​(java.lang.String textFieldGetter)
      Delete button also checks some conditions as number buttons and deletes the last character according to result. If there is an error on the screen, it does not delete the last screen.
      Parameters:
      textFieldGetter - which brings text from screen of calculator.

    • headButton

      public static void headButton​(java.lang.String textFieldGetter)
      Head button pushes the number to the stack if it is efficient. While pushing to stack, it deletes the thousand separators. After calculations, thousand separators are again added before showing on the screen.
      Parameters:
      textFieldGetter - which brings text from screen of calculator. Stack size is limited as 100, so numbers more than that cannot be pushed.
